# Quote and code

> Djot source goes in; pandoc JSON comes out.

``` rust
fn main() {
    println!("hello from djot-export");
}
```

# Citations

A `[X]{.cite}` span is rewritten to a pandoc `Cite` node, with `X` parsed as a
pandoc-markdown citation: a plain key [@smith2004]{.cite}, a suppressed author
[-@smith2004]{.cite}, a locator [@smith2004, pp. 33-35]{.cite}, a prefix
[see @smith2004]{.cite}, and multiple keys [@smith2004; @doe2010]{.cite}.

Resolve them downstream:

``` sh
djot-export examples/djot-export.dj | pandoc -f json -t markdown --citeproc --bibliography refs.json
```

# Table-shaped text

Tables are not the focus of the current exporter. Keep this section as plain
paragraph content when checking unsupported syntax behavior.

